HEADWORD: Diskless
<hw>Disk"less</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having no disk;
appearing as a point and not expanded into a disk, as the image of a
faint star in a telescope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>disklike</ent>⟦br⟧
